article.headline: MVSU 54, Texas Southern 50
article.story: BIRMINGHAM, Ala. (AP) -- Stanford Speech had a game-high 18 points and six rebounds to lead Mississippi Valley State to a 54-50 victory over Texas Southern Friday in the Southwestern Athletic Conference tournament semifinals. Texas Southern (14-17) led for much of the first half, but Mississippi Valley State (17-14) pulled ahead 20-18 on a 3-pointer by Tychicus Snow with 8:11 left in the first half and never gave up the lead again. The Tigers didn't give up the victory easily. They managed to tie the game four times in the second half and never let the Delta Devils lead by more than five points after the break. Mississippi Valley State led by just one point with 17 seconds to play. But two free throws by Speech with 15 seconds left and another free throw by Carl Lucas gave them the four point edge that sealed the victory. Speech led the Delta Devils' three double figure scorers. Jefferey Price had 15 points and Snow added 10. Richard Cannon snagged eight rebounds. Jacques Jones led the Tigers with 17 points and six rebounds. Sollie Norwood added 12 and Stpaul Latham added 10. Leonta Matthews had seven rebounds. Mississippi Valley State will face Jackson State Saturday for the championship and an automatic NCAA tournament berth.
